Let a_0 be the centre of contraction of A and let b_0 be the centre of contraction of Ba_0. Then we let the centre of contraction of \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}Bx be 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_0,b_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
. The necessary identifications are obtained from the contractibility of A and Ba_0 by the characterisation of identifications in dependent sums (, ).

